From d212838d055c2431fc2b7eee13248a2817841ddc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DARPAN Engineering <darpan@example.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 17:04:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ml): add Milestone 9.1 Dataset Generation Pipeline
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Generates a real ML training dataset from the existing Realtime +
Prediction engines — no fabricated data, no separate polling loop.

- ml/dataset/types.ts: DatasetRow (12 columns) + DatasetStats
- ml/dataset/csv-writer.ts: file I/O — auto-creates dataset.csv with
  header if missing, sync appends (safe on Node's single JS thread),
  real fs.stat for size/mtime
- ml/features/feature-engineering.ts: pure vehicle+prediction -> row
  join; nullable fields (speed/bearing/stop_sequence/delay) stay null
  when the feed genuinely doesn't report them, never fabricated
- ml/exporter/dataset-export.service.ts: throttles writes to a real 15s
  cadence, dedupes via snapshot-identity + a bounded vehicle_id:timestamp
  key set, lazily re-scans the existing file once per process for
  restart-safe stats
- app/api/ml/dataset/stats/route.ts: GET /api/ml/dataset/stats
  (totalRows, lastUpdated, fileSize, todaySamples)

Integration: one line in services/analytics/analytics.service.ts's
computeContext() passes the vehicles+predictions it already computed to
recordSnapshot() — no new fetch, no new prediction run, same pattern as
the existing recordTrendSnapshot() call right above it.

.gitignore: ignore /data/ml/ (generated output, not source).

Verified end-to-end against the real 5,356-vehicle sample feed:
auto-create + header + all 5,356 rows on first write, snapshot-identity
dedup confirmed (repeat call is a no-op), 15s throttle window confirmed
(call within window is a no-op), post-throttle append confirmed after a
real 16s wait (+10 rows, correctly counted as today's samples), and
restart-safety confirmed via a fresh process re-scanning the same file
(reports the exact prior totals).
